Instruction.1: Sit on the ground with a bench behind you. Have the barbell over your legs just above your hips.
Instruction.2: Lean back against the bench so that your shoulders are resting upon it, stretch your arms out to either side using the bench as support.
Instruction.3: Raise the weight by driving through your feet and extending your hips upwards. Support the weight with your shoulders and feet.
Instruction.4: Slowly extend as far as you can, and then slowly return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stance width can vary with a sumo DL. Some prefer toes near the plates. Others prefer a more narrow stance to get more drive off the floor.
Instruction.2: Make sure your arms are inside your legs. The bar should be just over your mid-foot. Flatten your back and push your heels into the floor.
Instruction.3: Try to extend your knees and hips simultaneously.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back on the floor with your knees bent and your feet flat on the ground. Place a barbell across your hips and grasp it with both hands.
Instruction.2: Keeping your arms straight, push through your heels to lift your hips off the ground and raise the barbell.
Instruction.3: Hold the bridge position for a moment, then slowly lower your hips back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a barbell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the barbell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the barbell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the barbell on the opposite side of your body.

WorkoutName: Barbell Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a box, the barbell placed over your hips, and cross one leg over the other.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a box, the barbell placed over your hips.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Barbell Feet Elevated Single Leg Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a box, the barbell placed over your hips. Raise one leg up and off the box.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Barbell Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a box, the barbell placed over your hips. Place one foot about 6-9 inches in front of the other.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your mid-foot under the bar and grip the bar with your hands, about a shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees, then lift the bar by straightening your back. It is important to keep your back straight.
Instruction.3: Stand to your full height and hold.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar to the floor by bending your knees and keeping your back straight.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Maintain the natural arch in your back, squeezing your shoulder blades and raising your chest.
Instruction.2: Grip the bar across your shoulders and support it on your upper back. Unwrack the bar by straightening your legs, and take a step back.
Instruction.3: Bend your knees as you lower the weight without altering the form of your back until your hips are below your knees.
Instruction.4: Raise the bar back to starting position, lift with your legs and exhale at the top.

Instruction.1: Place the barbell on your back
Instruction.2: Step your foot back and around while simultaneously bringing the weight down.
Instruction.3: Return to start and repeat on other leg.

Instruction.1: Find a box or bench that is roughly knee height or a few inches lower. (The lower the box is the lower the mobility requirement).
Instruction.2: You can either place your toes or the top of your foot on the box. Point your front foot forward or slightly turned outwards and break at the knees and hips simultaneously.
Instruction.3: Aim to get your front leg to hit parallel depth (hamstring parallel with the ground) or lower.
Instruction.4: The further forward your front foot is, the longer the Range of Motion is at your hips. The further back your front foot is, the longer the ROM at your knees.

Instruction.1: Measure your hands by the markings on the bar to make sure you're even. Then throw your elbows underneath the bar.
Instruction.2: The bar should be set so high on your shoulders it digs into your neck a bit. Make sure to push your elbows up to the ceiling for the entire rep. To make sure you don't get too pitched forward.
Instruction.3: Use the squat stance you would use for a back or goblet squat. Push your hips back to initiate the squat. Break at the knees until you hit parallel depth.
Instruction.4: Squat back up to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Measure your shoulders against the bar to make sure you're even. Throw your shoulders under the bar. The bar should be digging into your neck slightly.
Instruction.2: Make sure to push your elbows up to the ceiling for the entire rep. To make sure you don't get too pitched forward.
Instruction.3: Use the squat stance you would use for a back or goblet squat. Push your hips back to initiate the squat. Break at the knees until you hit parallel depth.
Instruction.4: Squat back up to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place the bar on your traps. You may need a pad so the bar doesn't dig into your cervical spine.
Instruction.2: Push your hips straight back. Your knees should stay MOSTLY extended (think soft knees). Also make sure to
Instruction.3: Look for what feels like a stretch in your hamstrings. The stretch feeling means you're likely nearing the end of your Range of Motion without rounding your spine.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch push your hips forward until you're in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place the bar between your traps and rear delts. Pull your shoulder blades back to give the bar a shelf to sit on.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. This means you're nearing the end of your Range of Motion with out rounding your spine.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch push your hips forward until you'e in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Take a shoulder width, double overhand or mixed grip.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place the bar on top of your traps.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees. Push your elbows forward to keep yourself from getting pitched too far forward.
Instruction.3: Aim to get your hamstrings to parallel with the floor.
Instruction.4: Push your heels into the floor and squat back to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Pull your shoulder blades back really hard and place the bar on your posterior delts.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees to initiate the squat.
Instruction.3: Aim to get your hamstrings to parallel with the ground. Push your heels into the floor and squat back up to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a barbell on the floor in front of you.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, positioning your hands just outside of your hips.
Instruction.3: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees.
Instruction.4: As you lift the barbell, pull your shoulders back and squeeze your glutes to fully extend your hips at the top of the movement.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell at your shoulders with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Step forward with your right foot and bend both knees to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell at your shoulders with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.
Instruction.3: Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.
Instruction.4: Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your heels on a plate or low step.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and feet on a plate. Place the bar in a front rack position.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your heels raised off the ground.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell at your shoulders with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Step out to the side with your right foot and bend your right knee to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat on the opposite side by stepping out with your left foot.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper back.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper back.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, pausing for a moment at the bottom of the movement before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with your toes pointed slightly outward.
Instruction.2: Place a barbell on the floor behind you, with the weight plates on either side.
Instruction.3: Bend down and grab the barbell with an overhand grip, your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your shoulders down as you grip the bar.
Instruction.4: Stand up straight, lifting the barbell off the ground and pulling it toward your hips. Keep your elbows close to your body and your shoulders down as you do this.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with a barbell on your shoulders. Your feet should be slightly pointed outward, and your shoulders should be down and relaxed.
Instruction.2: Step backward with one foot, lowering your body until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is hovering just above the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your back foot, returning to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with a barbell on your shoulders. Your feet should be slightly pointed outward, and your shoulders should be down and relaxed.
Instruction.2: Place a step or box beside you, and step up onto it with one foot. Your other foot should remain on the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your grounded foot, raising your body up onto the step.
Instruction.4: Step back down with the same foot, returning to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with your toes pointed slightly outward.
Instruction.2: Place a barbell on the floor in front of you, with the weight plates on either side. Make sure that the bar is directly in line with your feet.
Instruction.3: Bend down and grab the barbell with an overhand grip, your hands much wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your shoulders down as you grip the bar.
Instruction.4: Stand up straight, lifting the barbell off the ground and pulling it toward your hips. Keep your elbows close to your body and your shoulders down as you do this.
Instruction.5: Slowly lower the barbell back to the ground, making sure to keep your back straight and your shoulders down throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart. The bar should be in a rack or box so it's lifted off the ground.
Instruction.2: Grab the barbell with an overhand grip, your hands should be much wider than shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.3: Hing forward at the hips keeping your knees mostly extended. Hinge until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you are back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Take a large step forward with one leg, and lower your body until your back knee nearly touches the ground. Your front knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle, and your back leg should be straight.
Instruction.2: Push through the heel of your front foot to raise your body back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a barbell across your upper back and shoulders, using an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box, keeping your left foot off the ground.
Instruction.3: Step back down with your right foot, lowering your left foot to the ground.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a barbell across your upper back and shoulders, using an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box.
Instruction.3: Step back down with your right foot.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a barbell across your upper back and shoulders, using an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Sit back and lower your body down until your glutes tap the top of the box, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to extend your hips and stand up, bringing your body back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding a barbell in the crook of your elbows, with your palms facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and lower your torso forward until it is nearly parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to extend your hips and raise your body back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding a barbell in the crook of your arms, near your belly. Your palms should be facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Sit back and lower your body down until your thighs are parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to extend your hips and stand back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Set up the landmine attachment and load weight.
Instruction.2: Stand facing the landmine, holding the weight away from your chest.
Instruction.3: Step backward with one leg, lunge down while twisting your torso toward the front leg, return to starting position, and repeat on the other side.

WorkoutName: Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press

Instruction.1: Stand facing the landmine with feet hip-width apart and holding the end of the landmine barbell with both hands, keeping elbows bent and close to your body.
Instruction.2: Step backward with the right foot, lunge down, and press the landmine away from your chest.
Instruction.3: Push through the left heel to return to the starting position while pulling the landmine back to your chest.
Instruction.4: Repeat on the opposite side, alternating for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar at your side with one hand.
Instruction.2: With the leg on the same side of your body as the barbell, lunge backward and across your body at a 45 degree angle while keeping your weight on your front heel to lower your back knee gently to the ground.
Instruction.3: Drive through your front heel as you step back to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Start on your hands and knees perpendicular to the barbell with the end of the barbell resting on the inside of your knee that is closer to the bar.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core braced, your back flat, and your moving leg bent at a 90 degree angle, drive the heel of your working leg up the ceiling while squeezing your glute.
Instruction.3: Follow the movement path as you bring your knee back down to the ground beneath your hip, keeping your knee bent to maintain control of the barbell.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Start facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar in the goblet position in front of your chest with your elbows close to your sides.
Instruction.2: Step backward and across your body with one leg at a 45 degree angle while keeping your weight on your front heel to gently lower your back knee to the ground.
Instruction.3: Drive through your front heel as you step back up and to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching legs.

Instruction.1: Start facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar close to your chest in the goblet position with your elbows tucked in close to your body.
Instruction.2: Step directly out to the side with both toes pointing forward. Keep your weight on the heel of the leg you step out with as you sink down over that foot while your other leg remains straight for balance.
Instruction.3: Drive through the heel over which you have centered your body as you step back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Start facing away from the landmine attachment with the end of the barbell resting on one shoulder against the base of your neck while leaning slightly back into the weight of the barbell.
Instruction.2: Squat down with control while keeping the weight of the barbell as close to centered over your midpoint as possible, then drive through your heels to stand all the way back up and return to starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat for desired number of reps, then switch the side of your body the barbell is on every subsequent set.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the landmine with your feet shoulder width apart while holding the end of the barbell in your hands with your arms fully extended down towards the ground.
Instruction.2: While keeping your torso tall and core engaged, step directly out to one side, using the foot you have stepped out with to sit down into the lunge while keeping your other leg straight.
Instruction.3: Drive through your heel on your bent leg as your step together to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat for desired number of reps on the same side before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of the landmine with your feet hip-width apart and your back straight. Grasp the landmine barbell with one hand, holding it at at your side with your palm facing in towards your leg.
Instruction.2: Take a step backward with your foot on the same side that you're holding the barbell, lowering your body into a lunge position. Bend both knees to lower your body down until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, or as low as your flexibility allows. Keep your torso upright, your chest lifted, and your core engaged throughout the movement.
Instruction.3: Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position. Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the landmine attachment while holding the end of the bar with one hand at your shoulder on the same side with your elbow tucked to your body underneath your wrist.
Instruction.2: Step back with the leg on the same side that you are holding the bar on and with control lower yourself down into a lunge position while keeping your core engaged and torso tall, then drive through your front heel as you step back to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Once your feet are back in the starting position, drive the bar up overhead until your arm is fully extended, then lower the bar back down to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeated for the desired number of reps, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Stand with a barbell at your shins with your feet shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at your hips and keep your knees as fully extended as possible.
Instruction.3: Grab the barbell and then extend your hips while maintaining a straight back.
Instruction.4: From the standing position, lower the weight in a controlled manner.
Instruction.5: You can either lower the weight to the floor or before you touch the floor, depending on your mobility.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of the landmine with your feet hip-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with both hands, palms facing each other, and hold it in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and push your hips back, allowing the landmine to travel down your thighs. Lower the landmine by bending forward at the hips while keeping your back flat, allowing the barbell to move closer to the floor. Continue the movement until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, keeping your legs relatively straight but with a slight bend in the knees.
Instruction.3: Reverse the movement by pushing your hips forward and driving through your heels while keeping your back straight.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Stand perpendicularly to the barbell with the end of the bar in front of your feet. Squat down and hold the end of the bar with your hand closer to the landmine attachment with your palm facing your body.
Instruction.2: Drive your feet into the ground to start the motion. As your legs fully extend, pull the bar upwards with your hand and start to rotate your torso in towards the landmine attachment. As you do so, bring your other hand up to the bar and switch your grip. Press through the bar to extend your arm all the way upright, pivoting your back foot to allow for more trunk rotation.
Instruction.3: Perform the movement in reverse to return to the starting position. Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Setup a landmine with your back on a box.
Instruction.2: Lay the end of the bar over your hip.
Instruction.3: Push your hips toward the ceiling until you feel a contraction, then bring your hips back toward the floor.

Instruction.1: Grab the end of the landmine and stand perpendicular to the bar.
Instruction.2: Lift your inside leg and keep your outside leg planted.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back keeping your knees mostly extended. When you feel the stretch in your hams, push your hips forward until you are standing upright.

Instruction.1: Hold the end of the bar in front of you.
Instruction.2: Pop your hips, pull your elbows up to the ceiling, and get underneath the bar.

Instruction.1: Hold the end of the bar in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees.
Instruction.3: Reach at least parallel with the ground before pushing through your heels back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand in a staggered position. With the back leg bent and the front mostly extended.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back until you feel a stretch through your front hamstring.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back forward until you are standing.

Instruction.1: Stand with a wide stance and straddle over the end of the bar.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees, and grab the bar.
Instruction.3: Stand up with the bar.

Instruction.1: Hold the bar with a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and sink into a squat.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels and squat back up. Use the momentum you generate at the legs to push the bar over head.
Instruction.4: Let the bar return to the goblet position before starting the next rep.

WorkoutName: Barbell Figure Four Heels Elevated Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Put your shoulder blades on a bench and cross one leg over the other. Put one foot on a low box or plate.
Instruction.2: Start with your hips up.
Instruction.3: Drop your hips and then push your hips up toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Put your shoulder blades on a bench and cross one leg over the other.
Instruction.2: Start with your hips up.
Instruction.3: Drop your hips and then push your hips up toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Measure your shoulders against the bar to make sure you're even. Wrap a pair of lifting straps around the bar. Hold the ends of the straps. Throw your shoulders under the bar. The bar should be digging into your neck slightly.
Instruction.2: Make sure to push your elbows up to the ceiling for the entire rep. To make sure you don't get too pitched forward.
Instruction.3: Use the squat stance you would use for a back or goblet squat. Push your hips back to initiate the squat. Break at the knees until you hit parallel depth.
Instruction.4: Squat back up to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground with a bench behind you. Place both feet on a plate or low box. Have the barbell over your legs just above your hips.
Instruction.2: Lean back against the bench so that your shoulders are resting upon it, stretch your arms out to either side using the bench as support.
Instruction.3: Raise the weight by driving through your feet and extending your hips upwards. Support the weight with your shoulders and feet.
Instruction.4: Slowly extend as far as you can, and then slowly return to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Barbell Single Leg Heels Elevated Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Start by lying on a bench with your foot on a plate or low box and a barbell on your hips.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on a bench with your foot on the ground and a barbell on your hips.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, one foot slightly behind. Bar on your back.
Instruction.2: Lower into a squat, keeping weight on front heel.
Instruction.3: Return to standing, engaging glutes and core.

Instruction.1: Stand with your mid-foot under the bar, plates should be on blocks, and grip the bar with your hands, about a shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees, then lift the bar by straightening your back. It is important to keep your back straight.
Instruction.3: Stand to your full height and hold.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar to the floor by bending your knees and keeping your back straight.

Instruction.1: Set up for a standard deadlift, grip the barbell.
Instruction.2: Lift, pause at knee height.
Instruction.3: Hold briefly, then complete the lift; reset and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with your mid-foot under the bar, feet should be on a plate or elevated platform, and grip the bar with your hands, about a shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees, then lift the bar by straightening your back. It is important to keep your back straight.
Instruction.3: Stand to your full height and hold.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar to the floor by bending your knees and keeping your back straight.

Instruction.1: Stand centered over the barbell, feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grip the bar with both hands, one in front, one behind.
Instruction.3: Lift by driving through your heels, keeping your back straight, then lower slowly.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart with the bar on the ground at your side.
Instruction.2: Lift the bar to your side and walk for the allotted amount of time or distance.
Instruction.3: Set the bar down and switch sides.

Instruction.1: Set up for a sumo deadlift, grip the barbell.
Instruction.2: Lift, pause at knee height.
Instruction.3: Hold briefly, then complete the lift; reset and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the bar just outside your knees. Pull the bar from the floor by driving through your legs, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.2: As the bar reaches your hips, extend explosively, shrug, and drop under to catch it in a front squat position with elbows high. Stand up tall.
Instruction.3: Dip slightly, then drive through your legs to push the bar overhead.
Instruction.4: Stabilize the bar overhead, lock arms, then bring feet together before lowering the bar safely.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, and keep your back straight.
Instruction.2: Drive through your legs, extending your hips, knees, and ankles explosively while pulling the barbell upward.
Instruction.3: As the bar rises, pull it close to your body, leading with your elbows until it reaches chest level.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the barbell with a wide overhand grip, and keep your back straight and core engaged.
Instruction.2: Lift the barbell by explosively extending your hips, knees, and ankles while keeping the bar close to your body.
Instruction.3: As the bar reaches chest level, rotate your wrists and elbows up and back, transitioning into an overhead press.
Instruction.4: Fully extend your arms overhead, stabilize the bar, then lower it back to the starting position with control.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell over midfoot. Grip the bar wide (outside shoulders), hook grip recommended.
Instruction.2: Keep chest up, back straight, and drive through heels to lift the bar off the ground, keeping it close to your body.
Instruction.3: As the bar reaches mid-thigh, explode upwards by extending hips, knees, and ankles, shrugging shoulders and pulling the bar high.
Instruction.4: Drop under the bar slightly, catching it overhead with arms locked out. Stand up fully to complete the lift.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, barbell over midfoot. Grip the bar wide with an overhand grip, chest up, and back straight.
Instruction.2: Lift the bar by driving through your legs, keeping it close to your body. Extend your hips and knees while maintaining a straight back.
Instruction.3: Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles while shrugging your shoulders. Pull yourself under the bar as it moves upward.
Instruction.4: Drop into a deep squat while locking the bar overhead. Stabilize, then stand up fully to complete the lift.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, gripping the barbell with a wide (snatch-width) grip. Keep your back straight, chest up, and bar close to your body.
Instruction.2: Drive through your legs, extending your hips, knees, and ankles while pulling the barbell up explosively.
Instruction.3: Shrug your shoulders forcefully and pull the bar as high as possible, keeping elbows above the bar.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar back to the starting position in a controlled manner and reset for the next rep.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, barbell in front rack, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

Instruction.1: Have the barbell in a high bar position and place your foot on a plate or a low box.
Instruction.2: Put all of your weight on your front foot and lean forward.
Instruction.3: Lower until your calves touch your hamstrings and then extend back up.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet on a plate and holding a barbell in the crook of your arms, near your belly. Your palms should be facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Step back with one foot off the plate and lower your back knee to the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through your front leg and bring your back foot to the plate.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, barbell on your back, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, bar on your back, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

Instruction.1: Place your legs on the platform with your feet at shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Release the weight and extend your legs fully, without locking your knees.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight until your legs are at a 90° angle (but DO NOT allow your butt and lower back to rise off of the pad. This will put your lower back in a rounded position, which is very dangerous.)
Instruction.4: Raise the weight back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Position yourself in the hack squat machine with your back against the pad and shoulders under the shoulder pads.
Instruction.2: Place feet shoulder-width apart on the platform. Keep your back straight, and slowly lower into a squat position.
Instruction.3: Press through your heels to return to the starting position, keeping your core engaged. Repeat for desired reps and sets.

Instruction.1: Adjust machine settings to fit your height. Sit with back flat against pad, legs together.
Instruction.2: Slowly press legs apart against resistance. Pause at peak.
Instruction.3: Slowly return legs to starting position. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand on the platform and set the pad just over the opposing hip of the working leg.
Instruction.2: Place the working leg over the pad.
Instruction.3: Press your leg outward. Aim to get the longest range of motion possible.

Instruction.1: Adjust the machine for your height, sit with your back against the pad, knees bent, feet flat on the platform.
Instruction.2: Brace your core, push through your heels, and extend your hips upwards, lifting the weight while squeezing your glutes.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight slowly back to the starting position, ensuring controlled movement; repeat for desired reps and sets.

Instruction.1: Place your legs on the platform with your feet at shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Release the weight and extend your legs fully, without locking your knees.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight until your legs are at a 90° angle (but DO NOT allow your butt and lower back to rise off of the pad. This will put your lower back in a rounded position, which is very dangerous.)
Instruction.4: Raise the weight back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand on the platform and sideways on the machine.
Instruction.2: Place the pad at just above hip height. Place the working leg over the pad.
Instruction.3: Extend the working leg backwards and flex your glute at the end of each rep.

Instruction.1: Place your feet at the bottom the platform at shoulder width. Lift your heels up.
Instruction.2: Press against the platform and extend your legs fully, without locking your knees.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight until your legs are at a 90° angle (but DO NOT allow your butt and lower back to rise off of the pad. This will put your lower back in a rounded position, which is very dangerous.)
Instruction.4: Raise the weight back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Sit on the seat upright with your knees placed on the pads and your feet on the foot pads.
Instruction.2: Push your legs outwards and backwards and flex your glutes.

Instruction.1: Position yourself in the hack squat machine with your back against the pad and shoulders under the shoulder pads.
Instruction.2: Place feet shoulder-width apart on the platform.
Instruction.3: Press through your heels to the starting position, keeping your core engaged. Repeat for desired reps and sets.

Instruction.1: Put the belt around your waist and hook the end of the belt onto the machines.
Instruction.2: Stand up to disengage the holding mechanism. Hold the arms while you squat.
Instruction.3: Once you've completed your set, reset the holding mechanism.

Instruction.1: Grab the handles, place one knee on the pad, and the foot of the working leg on the foot plate.
Instruction.2: Push your working leg back until you feel your glute contract, then return to the starting position without resting the weights.

Instruction.1: Position yourself in the pendulum squat machine with your back against the pad and shoulders under the shoulder pads.
Instruction.2: Place feet shoulder-width apart on the platform. Keep your back straight, and slowly lower into a squat position.
Instruction.3: Press through your heels to return to the starting position, keeping your core engaged. Repeat for desired reps and sets.

Instruction.1: Adjust the machine for your height, sit with your back against the pad, knees bent, feet flat on the platform.
Instruction.2: Brace your core, push through your heels, and extend your hips upwards, lifting the weight while squeezing your glutes.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight slowly back to the starting position, ensuring controlled movement; repeat for desired reps and sets.

Instruction.1: Lay on the pad and place your feet on the foot plate.
Instruction.2: Lift the plate up and disengage the holding hook.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight. Stop before your lower back rounds off the pad.
Instruction.4: Press the weight back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay on the pad and grab the handles.
Instruction.2: Slip your legs into the belt loop.
Instruction.3: Push your legs back until they are horizontal with the ground.
Instruction.4: Lower back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: This particular leg press has two separate foot plates. There are holding pins on both sides. Engage the pin on one side.
Instruction.2: Lower the weight but stop before your lower back begins to round.
Instruction.3: Press back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place your legs on the platform with your feet at shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Release the weight and extend your legs fully, without locking your knees.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight until your legs are at a 90° angle (but DO NOT allow your butt and lower back to rise off of the pad. This will put your lower back in a rounded position, which is very dangerous.)
Instruction.4: Raise the weight back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Lay flat and bring your left leg to 90 degrees.
Instruction.2: Hold your left leg with both hands and slowly rotate your hips to the right hand side.
Instruction.3: Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Instruction.4: Switch sides and repeat.

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground and lay one leg flat and the other over the top.
Instruction.2: Hold your leg with the same side arm and slowly rotate your hips and back.
Instruction.3: Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Instruction.4: Switch sides and repeat.

Instruction.1: On your front, place one leg forward and then stretch out the same side arm across the mat/floor.
Instruction.2: Fully extend your leg and arm.
Instruction.3: Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Instruction.4: Switch sides and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the feet.
Instruction.2: Bend the knees and hips to pick up the plate, keeping the back straight and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Stand up, lock the hips and legs, and press the plate overhead with straight arms.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back to the starting position, keeping control of it, and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the feet.
Instruction.2: Bend the knees and hips to pick up the plate, keeping the back straight and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Stand up while pulling the plate towards the chest.
Instruction.4: Keep shoulder level while keeping the elbows high and in front of the plate.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, with a weight plate held in both hands at chest height.
Instruction.2: Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight and your weight in your heels.
Instruction.3: Go down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then pause for a moment.
Instruction.4: Hold the squat position for the desired amount of time, keeping the weight plate steady and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Hold the plate with both hands at chest height.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core tight and your chest up, squat down as low as you can go while keeping your feet flat on the ground.
Instruction.3: Hold the squat position and reach the plate forward, keeping your arms straight and your back straight.
Instruction.4: Return the plate to your chest while you hold the squat position and repeat reaching the plate in front of you

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the torso.
Instruction.2: Step back and across the body with the right foot, bending both legs to lower into a lunge position.
Instruction.3: Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat on the other side by stepping back and across with the left foot.
Instruction.5: Continue alternating sides for desired reps.

WorkoutName: Plate Single Leg Pinch Grip Deadlift

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and facing forwards. Grip the sides of a weight plate with your palms facing down.
Instruction.2: Balance on one foot, as you raise the weight keep your arms and back straight, while you bring your  other foot back towards the ground
Instruction.3: Keep four raised leg straight and in alignment with your back as you lower the plate back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart and the plate held in front of the torso.
Instruction.2: Take a step to the side with one foot, bending the knee and lowering the hips into a lunge.
Instruction.3: Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat on the other side by stepping to the other side with the other foot.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart and the plate held in front of the torso.
Instruction.2: Take a step forward with one foot, bending the front knee to lower the hips into a lunge.
Instruction.3: Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat on the other side by stepping forward with the other foot.

Instruction.1: Engage your core and straighten your legs to lift the plate off the ground.
Instruction.2: Stand on one leg, keeping the other leg off the ground, while holding the plate in front of your body.
Instruction.3: Keep your back straight and maintain a neutral head position while looking straight ahead.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back down to the ground while keeping your balance on one leg.

Instruction.1: Stand on a plate with both feet.
Instruction.2: Step back with one foot to the floor and let your back knee get close to or tap the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through your front leg until both feet are back on the plate.

WorkoutName: Plate Glute Bridge to Chest Press

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with a plate on your chest.
Instruction.2: Push your hips up toward the ceiling and maintain that extended position.
Instruction.3: With your hips up, press the plate toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with a plate on your chest.
Instruction.2: Push your hips up toward the ceiling and maintain that extended position.
Instruction.3: Extend your elbows mostly, break at the shoulder joint while maintaining hip extension and the slight bend in your elbows.
Instruction.4: Let the plate tap the floor (or get close) and then pull the plate back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand tall with a plate overhead.
Instruction.2: Step with one foot forward bringing your back knee to the floor. Gently tap your knee then drive through your front leg.
Instruction.3: Go back to a standing position and then step forward with the opposing legs.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a weight plate.
Instruction.2: Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the plate towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.4: Once the plate is below your knees, drive through your heels to stand back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding two plates with a pinch grip.
Instruction.2: Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the plates towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Start with the plate at chest height. Begin a squat.
Instruction.2: Make sure to hit parallel depth. On your way back up, use the momentum you generate with your legs to help push the plate into an overhead position.
Instruction.3: Let the plate return to chest height before initiating the next squat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, the plate in front of the feet, and the knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Bend the hips and knees to grip the plate with palms facing the body.
Instruction.3: Keeping the back straight, stand up while lifting the plate off the ground.
Instruction.4: Return the plate back to the starting position by bending the hips and knees, keeping control of the plate.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, the plate held behind the neck and the knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips, keeping the back straight, until the torso is parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through the hips to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, the plate held in front of you, and the knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips, keeping the back straight, until the torso is parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through the hips to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold a weight plate at arm's length overhead, with your arms fully extended. The plate should be directly above your head and your elbows should be locked.
Instruction.2: Begin to bend your knees, lowering your body as far as you can while keeping the weight plate overhead. Make sure to keep your back straight and your chest lifted.
Instruction.3: Once your thighs are parallel to the ground or as low as you can go, pause for a moment.
Instruction.4: Push through your heels to return to a standing position, keeping the weight plate overhead the entire time.

Instruction.1: Hold the plate at chest height close to your body
Instruction.2: Take a big step backwards with your left leg, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground and your right knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.
Instruction.3: Push through your right heel to return to standing, bringing your left leg back to starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement on the other side, stepping backwards with your right leg and lowering your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground and your left knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.

Instruction.1: Step back with your right foot into a lunge position, both knees bent at 90 degrees.
Instruction.2: Twist your torso to the right, keeping the plate close to your chest.
Instruction.3: Push through your front foot to return to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and hold a weight plate in front of your chest with both hands.
Instruction.2: Keep your back straight, lower your body as if you were sitting back into a chair.
Instruction.3: Go as low as you can while keeping your heels flat on the ground, then push through your heels to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Lower into a squat position, keeping the plate at chest height.
Instruction.2: Slowly curl the plate towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Instruction.3: Hold for a moment at the top of the curl before lowering the plate back to chest height.
Instruction.4: Repeat the curls as you hold the squat position.

Instruction.1: Stand holding a weight plate at chest height with both hands.
Instruction.2: Lower into a squat, extending the plate in front of you at chest height
Instruction.3: As you stand back up, pull the plate back into your chest.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, Holding a plate to your chest, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell. Hold a plate up to your chest.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position with Bosu under feet.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg back, squeezing glutes.
Instruction.3: Lower the leg back down and switch sides.

WorkoutName: Bosu Ball Feet Elevated Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Lie on back, place feet on Bosu, knees bent.
Instruction.2: Lift hips and squeeze glutes.
Instruction.3: Lower hips back down to complete one rep.

Instruction.1: Stand on Bosu with feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Drop into squat position and place hands on Bosu.
Instruction.3: Jump feet back into plank, perform a pushup, then jump back to squat.

Instruction.1: Stand on Bosu with feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Drop into squat position and place hands on Bosu.
Instruction.3: Jump feet back to plank, then jump back to squat.

Instruction.1: Sit on Bosu, lean back, hands on the floor.
Instruction.2: Drive hips upward, squeezing glutes.
Instruction.3: Lower hips back down to complete one rep.

Instruction.1: Stand on Bosu, step sideways into a lunge.
Instruction.2: Bend knee, keeping the other leg straight.
Instruction.3: Push off the bent leg, return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball at chest.
Instruction.2: Step back into lunge position.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position. Repeat on other leg.

WorkoutName: Bosu Ball Single Leg Elevated Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Lie on back, place one foot on Bosu, knee bent.
Instruction.2: Lift hips, squeezing glutes, one leg extended.
Instruction.3: Lower hips back down and switch legs.

WorkoutName: Bosu Ball Single Leg Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Sit on Bosu, lean back, one foot on the floor.
Instruction.2: Drive hips upward, squeezing glutes, one leg extended.
Instruction.3: Lower hips back down and switch legs.

Instruction.1: Take a split stance. Make sure to keep your chest tall.
Instruction.2: Bring your rear knee to the floor or close to it.
Instruction.3: Drive through your front heel and your rear foot back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand on Bosu, feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Squat down, keeping knees aligned with toes.
Instruction.3: Push through heels to stand back up.

WorkoutName: Bosu Ball Hand Sideplank Hip Abduction

Instruction.1: Start in a side plank with hand on Bosu.
Instruction.2: Lift the top leg while keeping the body stable.
Instruction.3: Lower the leg back down.

Instruction.1: Take a large step forward with one leg until your shoulders are under the smith machine
Instruction.2: lower your body until your back knee nearly touches the ground. Your front knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle, and your back leg should be straight.
Instruction.3: Push through the heel of your front foot to raise your body back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.2: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Start on your hands and knees with one foot placed on the bottom of the bar.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core braced, your back flat, and your moving leg bent at a 90 degree angle, drive the heel of your working leg up the ceiling while squeezing your glute.
Instruction.3: Follow the movement path as you bring your knee back down to the ground beneath your hip, keeping your knee bent to maintain control of the bar.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground with a bench behind you. Have the bar over your legs just above your hips.
Instruction.2: Lean back against the bench so that your shoulders are resting upon it, stretch your arms out to either side using the bench as support.
Instruction.3: Raise the weight by driving through your feet and extending your hips upwards. Support the weight with your shoulders and feet.
Instruction.4: Slowly extend as far as you can, and then slowly return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place your legs on the bar with your feet at shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Release the weight and extend your legs fully, without locking your knees.
Instruction.3: Lower the weight until your legs are at a 90° angle (but DO NOT allow your butt and lower back to rise off of the floor. This will put your lower back in a rounded position, which is very dangerous.)
Instruction.4: Raise the weight back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Place the bar on top of your traps. Take a narrow stance.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees. Push your elbows forward to keep yourself from getting pitched too far forward.
Instruction.3: Aim to get your hamstrings to parallel with the floor.
Instruction.4: Push your heels into the floor and squat back to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with the bar on your shoulders. Your feet should be slightly pointed outward, and your shoulders should be down and relaxed.
Instruction.2: Step backward with one foot, lowering your body until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is hovering just above the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your back foot, returning to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Take a shoulder width, double overhand or mixed grip.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

WorkoutName: Smith Machine Single Leg Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Start by lying on a bench with your foot on the ground and a barbell on your hips.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stance width can vary with a sumo DL. Some prefer toes near the plates. Others prefer a more narrow stance to get more drive off the floor.
Instruction.2: Make sure your arms are inside your legs. The bar should be just over your mid-foot. Flatten your back and unrack the bar
Instruction.3: Leave your knees mostly extended and flex and extend your hips.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Maintain the natural arch in your back and put the bar on your back. Squeezing your shoulder blades and raise your chest.
Instruction.2: Grip the bar across your shoulders and support it on your upper back. Unwrack the smith machine by straightening your legs.
Instruction.3: Bend your knees as you lower the weight without altering the form of your back until your hips are below your knees.
Instruction.4: Raise the bar back to starting position, lift with your legs and exhale at the top.

Instruction.1: Place your shoulder blades against a box or bench that won't move.
Instruction.2: Both your feet should be planted and your heels should not come off the floor. Point your toes forward.
Instruction.3: Break at the hips. Seek the longest range of motion possible. Focus on the top end of the movement. Push your hips as high as possible on each rep.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with both feet planted. Make sure you keep your heels glued to the floor.
Instruction.2: Place the dumbbell on your hips. Push your hips toward the ceiling until you feel your glutes contract.
Instruction.3: Then return to the floor.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with one leg crossed over the other and your heel planted on the ground.
Instruction.2: Push your hips toward the ceiling and hold for a second.

Instruction.1: Put your shoulder blades on a bench and cross one leg over the other.
Instruction.2: Start with your hips up.
Instruction.3: Drop your hips and then push your hips up toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell on your hips.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell on your hips.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your feet on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Place one foot on the ground and the other slightly in front, with your knees bent.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, raise your hips up off the ground by pushing through your heels and squeezing your glutes.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back on a bench with your feet on the ground and a dumbbell on your hips.
Instruction.2: Place one foot on the ground and the other slightly in front, with your knees bent.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, raise your hips up off the ground by pushing through your heels and squeezing your glutes.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a box, the dumbbell placed over your hips, and cross one leg over the other.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet on top of a sturdy box, bench or elevated surface. Place a dumbbell over your hips.
Instruction.2: Drive through your heels to lift your hips off the floor, making sure to keep your feet and knees pointing forward.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Single Leg Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a box, the dumbbell placed over your hips. Raise one leg up and off the box.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet in a staggered position on the box.
Instruction.2: Drive through your heels to lift your hips off the floor, making sure to keep your feet and knees pointing forward.

Instruction.1: Stand with a dumbbell held on the side of your leg.
Instruction.2: Raise that leg laterally as high as your hip range of motion allows for.

Instruction.1: Hold the weight tucked into your upper chest area, keeping your elbows in. Your feet should be slightly wider than shoulder width.
Instruction.2: Sink down into the squat, keeping your elbows inside the track of your knees.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels while keeping your chest up and return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold the dumbbell in a goblet position. With your elbows directly under your fists.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended. You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Holding the dumbbell in a goblet squat place your foot on a bench or box.
Instruction.2: Break at the hips and knees. Try to go to the point where your hamstring is parallel with the ground. Or until your back knee taps the floor.
Instruction.3: Make sure to keep your back flat and your elbows directly under your fists.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width stance. Push your butt back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended.
Instruction.2: You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings. When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward to complete the rep.
Instruction.3: Do not push your hips all the way forward. This will hyperextend your spine. Just go to a normal standing position.

Instruction.1: Find a box or bench that is roughly knee height or a few inches lower. (The lower the box is the lower the mobility requirement).
Instruction.2: You can either place your toes or the top of your foot on the box. Point your front foot forward or slightly turned outwards and break at the knees and hips simultaneously.
Instruction.3: Aim to get your front leg to hit parallel depth (hamstring parallel with the ground) or lower.
Instruction.4: The further forward your front foot is, the longer the Range of Motion is at your hips. The further back your front foot is, the longer the ROM at your knees.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other.
Instruction.2: Take a big step forward with your right foot, lowering your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the ground and your left knee is hovering just above the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through your right heel to straighten your right leg and return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Holding the dumbbell in a goblet squat place your foot on a bench or box.
Instruction.2: Break at the hips and knees. Try to go to the point where your hamstring is parallel with the ground. Or until your back knee taps the floor.
Instruction.3: Make sure to keep your back flat and your elbows directly under your fists.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Step your left foot behind and to the right of your right foot, crossing it behind your right leg.
Instruction.3: Bend your knees and lower your hips down and back, as if you were about to sit in a chair.
Instruction.4: Push through your right heel to straighten your right leg and return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Step forward with one of your legs while bending at your back leg. Bring your back knee to the floor or close to the floor.
Instruction.3: Push through your front leg explosively to get back to your starting position.

Instruction.1: Engage your core by drawing your belly button towards your spine. This will help to stabilize your body. Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Take a large step to the side with your right foot, planting it firmly on the ground.
Instruction.3: As you step, bend your right knee and lower your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. Your left leg should remain straight.
Instruction.4: Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat on the opposite side by stepping out with your left foot.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Take a big step backwards with your left leg, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground and your right knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.
Instruction.3: Push through your right heel to return to standing, bringing your left leg back to starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement on the other side, stepping backwards with your right leg and lowering your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground and your left knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Take a large step forward with one leg, and lower your body until your back knee nearly touches the ground. Your front knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle, and your back leg should be straight.
Instruction.3: Push through the heel of your front foot to raise your body back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Engage your core by drawing your belly button towards your spine. This will help to stabilize your body. Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Take a large step to the side with your right foot and reach toward the floor with your single dumbbell.
Instruction.3: As you step, bend your right knee and lower your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. Your left leg should remain straight.
Instruction.4: Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat on the opposite side by stepping out with your left foot.

Instruction.1: Hold two dumbbells by your side.
Instruction.2: Take a big step backwards with your left leg, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground and your right knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.
Instruction.3: Push through your right heel to return to standing, bringing your left leg back to starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement on the other side, stepping backwards with your right leg and lowering your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground and your left knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Take a large step forward with one leg, and lower your body until your back knee nearly touches the ground. Your front knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle, and your back leg should be straight.
Instruction.3: Push through the heel of your front foot to raise your body back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place two dumbbells on your shoulders and make sure you force your elbows upward.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees.
Instruction.3: When you reach parallel (hamstrings parallel with the ground) pause for 1-3 seconds. Then push through your heels back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place two dumbbells on your shoulders and push your elbows upward.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and break at the knees.
Instruction.3: Hit parallel depth and then drive through your heels back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell in goblet position.
Instruction.2: Squat down to parallel depth and then halfway back up.
Instruction.3: Stay in this short range of motion for the duration of the set.

Instruction.1: Take a half kneeling stance. The dumbbell should start over your knee that is up.
Instruction.2: Rotate at the spine and point the dumbbell to the opposing side.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Heels Up Narrow Goblet Squat

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet on a plate. Your feet should be very close to one another, but not touching.
Instruction.2: Begin your squat by pushing your hips back and breaking at the knees. Try to keep your chest tall while squatting.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell over one shoulder.
Instruction.2: Initiate the squat by pushing your hips back.
Instruction.3: Avoid doing any twisting. Try to keep your shoulders even.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift

Instruction.1: Start by standing on one leg with a dumbbell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Slowly bend at the hips and lower the dumbbell towards the ground while extending your free leg behind you.
Instruction.3: Keep your core engaged and your back straight as you lower the weight.
Instruction.4: Once the dumbbell is close to the ground, push through your heel to return to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift

Instruction.1: Start by standing on one leg with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding two dumbbells.
Instruction.2: From this starting position, hinge at the hips to lower the dumbbell towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Once you feel a stretch in your hamstring, slowly return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your standing leg slightly bent and avoid rounding your back as you lower the dumbbell.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Place one foot slightly behind the other, with the heel of your back foot elevated on a step or weight plate.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend at the hips and knees to lower the dumbbells towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Instruction.4: Once the dumbbells are below your knees, drive through your heels to stand back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Place the dumbbells on the ground between your feet.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in both hands.
Instruction.2: Bend your knees slightly and hinge at the hips to swing the dumbbell between your legs.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, explosively extend your hips and swing the dumbbell up to chest height.
Instruction.4: Allow the momentum of the swing to carry the dumbbell back down between your legs, and then repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Bring the dumbbells to your shoulders, with your palms facing inward and your elbows bent.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, dip your knees slightly and then quickly extend them as you press the dumbbells upwards.
Instruction.4: As you press the dumbbells upwards, also push your hips forward to help generate additional power.
Instruction.5: Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and hold two dumbbells overhead with both hands, using an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Begin the squat by bending at the hips and knees, keeping your core tight and the dumbbells balanced overhead.
Instruction.3: Lower your body as far as you can while keeping the dumbbells overhead, then push back up to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, making sure to keep your back straight, chest lifted, and the dumbbells stable overhead throughout the entire movement.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell in your right hand, extending it overhead.
Instruction.2: Inhale and begin to squat down, keeping the dumbbell overhead and your back straight.
Instruction.3: Go down as far as you can while still maintaining control, then exhale and return to standing position, keeping the dumbbell overhead. Repeat for desired reps and then switch to the other arm.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width stance holding one dumbbell. Push your butt back while leaving your knees MOSTLY extended.
Instruction.2: Reach toward the opposing leg. You should feel a stretch in your hamstrings. When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward to complete the rep.
Instruction.3: Do not push your hips all the way forward. This will hyperextend your spine. Just go to a normal standing position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Figure Four Heels Elevated Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a box, the barbell placed over your hips, and cross one leg over the other.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold two dumbbells at your shoulders with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.
Instruction.3: Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.
Instruction.4: Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing beside a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a dumbbell with a goblet grip.
Instruction.2: Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box.
Instruction.3: Step back down with your right foot.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a dumbbell with a goblet grip.
Instruction.2: Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box.
Instruction.3: Step back down with your right foot.

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground with a bench behind you. Place both feet on a plate or low box. Have the dumbbell over your legs just above your hips.
Instruction.2: Lean back against the bench so that your shoulders are resting upon it, stretch your arms out to either side using the bench as support.
Instruction.3: Raise the weight by driving through your feet and extending your hips upwards. Support the weight with your shoulders and feet.
Instruction.4: Slowly extend as far as you can, and then slowly return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with a dumbbell in your hands. Your feet should be slightly pointed outward, and your shoulders should be down and relaxed.
Instruction.2: Place a step or box beside you, and step up onto it with one foot. Your other foot should remain on the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your grounded foot, raising your body up onto the step.
Instruction.4: Step back down with the same foot, returning to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold one dumbbell on your shoulder with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.
Instruction.3: Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.
Instruction.4: Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold one dumbbell on your side with a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.
Instruction.3: Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.
Instruction.4: Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Leg Heels Elevated Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Start by lying on a bench with your foot on a plate or low box and a dumbbell on your hips.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold two dumbbells on your side with a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.
Instruction.3: Bring your left foot up onto the bench and stand up straight, keeping the barbell at your shoulders.
Instruction.4: Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, to return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, one foot slightly behind. Hold dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Lower into a squat, keeping weight on front heel.
