Instruction.3: Return to standing, engaging glutes and core.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart with a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand tall, holding dumbbells by your sides, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step forward with one leg, lowering until both knees form 90° angles.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, and switch legs.

Instruction.1: Hold one dumbbell with one or both hands, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step out to one side, bending the knee.
Instruction.3: Push off, return to center, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Hold two dumbbells by your side.
Instruction.2: Take a big step backwards with your left leg, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground and your right knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.
Instruction.3: Push back up and switch legs, alternating each rep.

Instruction.1: Grab a stick of some sort or hold onto something stable (rack, bench).
Instruction.2: Grab a box that is knee height or slightly lower.
Instruction.3: Hold the stick in your right arm, dumbbell in the other and put your right leg on the box.
Instruction.4: Begin your squat by breaking at the knees. Get your knee close to the floor or all the way to the floor. Make sure to keep your chest tall.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell at your chest, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step one leg diagonally back into a lunge.
Instruction.3: Alternate legs, keeping your chest up and core engaged.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width. Dumbbells at your side.
Instruction.2: Step forward with your right foot and bend both knees to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Step back with the same leg until the back knee taps the floor.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, dumbbells in both hands, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Front Rack Deficit Reverse Lunge

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, dumbbells in front rack position, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, dumbbell in a goblet position, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start.

Instruction.1: Place your front foot on a low box and take a split stance. Put all of your weight on your front foot.
Instruction.2: Break at the knees and lower yourself until your calves touch your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: Push yourself back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, dumbbells in both hands, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Front Rack Curtsy Deficit Lunge

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, dumbbells in front rack, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Front Rack Stability Ball Wall Squat

Instruction.1: Place a stability ball against a wall at about hip height.
Instruction.2: Hold two dumbbells in front rack position.
Instruction.3: Break at the hips and knees until you hit parallel or just below, then squat back up.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, dumbbell in goblet squat position, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.
Instruction.4: Stand on a platform, dumbbell in goblet squat position, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.5: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.6: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

Instruction.1: Place a stability ball against a wall at about hip height.
Instruction.2: Hold two dumbbells in each hand.
Instruction.3: Break at the hips and knees until you hit parallel or just below, then squat back up.

Instruction.1: Place a stability ball against a wall at about hip height.
Instruction.2: Hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.3: Break at the hips and knees until you hit parallel or just below, then squat back up.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Half Kneeling Goblet Romanian Deadlift

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a dumbbell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a dumbbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball at one shoulder, feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Squat down, keeping ball on same side throughout movement.
Instruction.3: Stand back up, squeezing glutes. Repeat on other side.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding medicine ball close.
Instruction.2: Squat down, keeping ball close to head and chest.
Instruction.3: Stand back up, squeezing glutes. Repeat for desired reps.

WorkoutName: Medicine Ball Clean And Press Slam

Instruction.1: Hold the medicine ball with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Lift the ball explosively, clean it to shoulder height.
Instruction.3: Press the ball overhead, then slam it to the ground.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball overhead.
Instruction.2: Step back into lunge position.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position. Repeat on other leg.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball overhead.
Instruction.2: Squat down, keeping back straight.
Instruction.3: Stand back up. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball at chest.
Instruction.2: Step back into lunge position.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position. Repeat on other leg.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball while standing on one leg.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward on one leg, extending other leg behind.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position. Repeat on other leg.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball at chest.
Instruction.2: Squat down, reach ball to one side.
Instruction.3: Stand up and repeat reach on other side.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball at chest, facing wall.
Instruction.2: Squat down, then throw ball at wall.
Instruction.3: Catch and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Toss medicine ball up, catch with both hands.
Instruction.2: Repeat toss and catch for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball at chest.
Instruction.2: Step back into lunge position, extend your arms, twist torso.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position. Repeat on other leg.

Instruction.1: Stand tall with a medicine ball held against one hip.
Instruction.2: Lift the leg on the opposite side laterally.
Instruction.3: Lower the leg and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball.
Instruction.2: Step laterally, performing a lunge, then slam the ball.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball at chest.
Instruction.2: Jump, extending arms overhead.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the bottom.
Instruction.2: Face sideways with the ankle attachment on your outside leg. Walk a few steps away.
Instruction.3: Abduct at the hips and raise your leg out to the side.
Instruction.4: Return to the starting position and stop just short of your foot touching back to the ground (to keep tension on the muscle).

WorkoutName: Cable Standing Straight Leg Glute Kickback

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to the bottom of the crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment .
Instruction.2: Get your elbows directly underneath the bar, squat straight up and then walk back a few steps.
Instruction.3: Break at your knees and hips to initiate the squat. Make sure you maintain a flat back.
Instruction.4: Squat all the way back to a standing position.

Instruction.1: You can use a straight or EZ bar on this exercise. Cable should be set all to the bottom.
Instruction.2: Grab the attachment and walk back a few steps. Take a split stance. One leg in front and one behind.
Instruction.3: Break at the knees and hips to initiate the split squat. Make sure your back knee touches the floor.
Instruction.4: Squat back up into a standing position.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar or ez bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back
Instruction.2: Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.
Instruction.2:
Push your butt back to initiate the movement while lifting one of your legs.
Then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: Compete your given amount of reps, then switch to opposite leg.
Instruction.4: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back.

Instruction.1: This exercise works best with a rope attachment but can be done with anything. The attachment should be set to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2:
Face away from the cable machine, straddle the cable itself, and grab the attachment.
Walk a few steps away.
Instruction.3: Break at the hips while maintaining a flat back and mostly extended knees.
Instruction.4: Push hips forward until you are back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.
Instruction.2: Stand with a staggered stance. Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. Bring a bench over to the cables. The cable should be set to hip height.
Instruction.2: Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Start with handles set to the bottom of the machine. Grab a box, stand on top of the box, squat the weight up into a standing position.
Instruction.2: Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Instruction.3: To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

WorkoutName: Cable Incline Bench Straight Leg Kickback

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. Bring a bench over to the cables. Put the bench at incline level. The cable should be set to shoulder height.
Instruction.2: Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment .
Instruction.2: Place the bar in your elbows, squat straight up and then walk back a few steps.
Instruction.3: Break at your knees and hips to initiate the squat. Make sure you maintain a flat back.
Instruction.4: Squat all the way back to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the bottom.
Instruction.2: Take a quadruped position with the cable going across your planted leg.
Instruction.3: Abduct at the hips and raise your leg out to the side.
Instruction.4: Return to the starting position and stop just short of the cables touching back down (to keep tension on the muscle).

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set halfway up the crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Start with a bent knee position. Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet about hip-width apart and holding the bar in the crook of your elbows, with your palms facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and lower your torso forward until it is nearly parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to extend your hips and raise your body back to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Cable Standing Straight Leg Mid Kickback

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to halfway up the crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Bring the cable all the way to the bottom of the stack. Use an ankle attachment.
Instruction.2: Keeping your feet together, move your legs out to the sides and then back to the midline of your body. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

Instruction.1: Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to the bottom of the crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Break at the knee, push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Instruction.3: Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

Instruction.1: Put on a dip belt and attach the strap/ chain to the cable's carabiner.
Instruction.2: Take a few steps back and take a split stance.
Instruction.3: Lower into a split squat, letting the weight pull you forward. As you squat back to the starting position push yourself backwards against the resistance.

Instruction.1: Put on a dip belt. Attach the strap/chain to the cable's carabiner.
Instruction.2: Take a few steps back. Begin to squat by flexing at the knees and hips.
Instruction.3: Let the weight pull you forward as you squat. Then push your toes through the front of your shoes as you squat back to the start position.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back with your feet in the foot cradles of the TRX straps, with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground.
Instruction.2: Place your arms by your sides with your palms facing down.
Instruction.3: Drive your hips up towards the ceiling, squeezing your glutes and hamstrings at the top of the movement.

Instruction.1: Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding onto the TRX handles with both hands.
Instruction.2: Step your left foot behind your right, crossing it behind your right leg, and lower yourself into a curtsy lunge.
Instruction.3: Push through your right foot to return to the starting position and repeat the movement with the other leg.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the TRX straps and place your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Begin by lowering into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips, keeping your back straight and chest up.
Instruction.3: Explosively jump up off the ground, using your arms for momentum if desired.
Instruction.4: Land softly back in the squat position, making sure to absorb the impact with your legs.

Instruction.1: Grasp the TRX handles with both hands and extend your arms straight in front of you.
Instruction.2: Step laterally to one side, keeping your arms extended and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower your body into a lunge position, keeping your front knee bent at a 90-degree angle and your back leg straight.
Instruction.4: Push off your front foot to return to the starting position, keeping your arms extended and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Hold on to the TRX straps and step away until the strap is taut.
Instruction.2: Step backwards with one leg in to a lunge position and gently tap your knee to the floor.
Instruction.3: Lunge back to the starting position and repeat with the other leg.

Instruction.1: Hold the two TRX straps and step away until the straps are taut. Take a split stance.
Instruction.2: Bring your back knee to the floor and gently tap the floor.
Instruction.3: Use your arms and the TRX to help assist you getting back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold the two TRX straps and lean away from the anchor point.
Instruction.2: Flex at the hips and knees in to a squat position.
Instruction.3: You can use your arms and the straps to assist you back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Set up the Vitruvian, including a the provided belt.
Instruction.2: Position yourself with feet shoulder-width apart on the Vitruvian.
Instruction.3: Perform the squat by bending at the knees and hips, lowering your body until thighs are parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Return to the starting position by extending your knees and hips, pushing through your feet.

Instruction.1: Stand tall with both feet on the platform.
Instruction.2: Step backwards and bring your back knee to the floor.

Instruction.1: Wear the belt attachment.
Instruction.2: Cross one leg over the other, and then press your hips toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Use the bar attachment.
Instruction.2: Place the bar over your front delts and cross your arms.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back and aim to hit parallel depth.

Instruction.1: Put your back on the bench.
Instruction.2: Place the bar or belt over your hips.
Instruction.3: Flex and extend your hips fully on each rep.

Instruction.1: Take an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Keep your knees mostly extended and hinge forward at the hips.
Instruction.3: Keep a flat back.

Instruction.1: Hold medicine ball while standing on one leg.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward on one leg, extending other leg behind.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position. Repeat on other leg.

Instruction.1: Place one foot firmly on the ground and one foot behind the other. Bend the knee on your back leg.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward until you feel a stretch in your front leg.

Instruction.1: Stabilise yourself in the side lying position, using your upper arm and under leg
Instruction.2: Raise your upper leg till it is parallel to the ground. This is your starting point.
Instruction.3: Raise your leg and lower back to parallel for the specified amount of reps and/or sets
Instruction.4: Feel your bum (glute med) and the lateral line of your leg worked

WorkoutName: Abductor Leg Raise Side Lying Isometric

Instruction.1: Stabilise yourself in the side lying position, using your upper arm and under leg
Instruction.2: Raise your upper leg till it is parallel to the ground and hold isometrically for the specified amount of time.
Instruction.3: Feel your bum (glute med) and the lateral line of your leg worked

Instruction.1: Lay on your side with knees bent. 90° angle at hips, knees and feet.
Instruction.2: Externally rotate the top knee without dropping your hip back
Instruction.3: Hold for a split second (or as indicated by therapist/trainer) and return to starting position without resting on the under knee

Instruction.1: Lay on your side with knees bent. 90° angle at hips, knees and feet.
Instruction.2: Lift your top leg slightly so no support is coming from the under leg.
Instruction.3: Externally rotate the top knee without dropping your hip back
Instruction.4: Hold for a split second (or as indicated by therapist/trainer) and return to starting position

WorkoutName: Clamshells 3 Internal External Rotations Side Lying

Instruction.1: Lay on your side with knees bent. 90° angle at hips, knees and feet.
Instruction.2: Lift your top leg a few centimeters off of the under leg (15-20cm)
Instruction.3: Externally rotate the top knee without dropping your hip back.
Instruction.4: Hold for a split second (or as indicated by therapist/trainer) and then internally rotate the knee

Instruction.1: Lay on your side with knees bent and a loop band around them. 90° angle at hips, knees and feet.
Instruction.2: Externally rotate the top knee without dropping your hip back
Instruction.3: Hold for a split second (or as indicated by therapist/trainer) and return to starting position without resting on the under knee

Instruction.1: Balance on one leg
Instruction.2: Try to tap your targets with the toes of your suspended leg
Instruction.3: The goal is to maintain balance while moving your leg towards the target and back

WorkoutName: Core Stability 1 Crosslateral Limb Raise 4Pt Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to the 4 point position (on all fours)
Instruction.2: 90° angles at hips and shoulder and neutral spine
Instruction.3: Raise opposite limbs till they are parallel to the ground
Instruction.4: Hold for a split second and bring back to starting position

WorkoutName: Core Stability 4 Crosslateral Limb Raise Push Up Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to a strict push-up position
Instruction.2: Maintain a toe placement roughly at shoulder width (the wider the leg stance the easier the exercise - the narrower the stance the more difficult it becomes.
Instruction.3: Tap your opposite shoulder with your fingertips.
Instruction.4: Do not tilt or shift your hips. Do not round or arch your back.

WorkoutName: Core Stability 5 Crosslateral Limb Raise Into Knee Elbow Tuck Push Up Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to a strict push-up position
Instruction.2: Raise opposite limbs till they are parallel to the ground
Instruction.3: Hold for a split second and then try to bring your elbow to your opposite knee by driving both towards the centre of the body.
Instruction.4: Spine might curve slightly but you should not shift your hips during the movement.

WorkoutName: Core Stability Regression Crosslateral Limb Raise Push Up Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to a strict push-up position
Instruction.2: Tap the hand of the working arm on the ground to find your balance. Raise opposite limbs till they are parallel to the ground
Instruction.3: Hold for a split second and then try to bring your elbow to your opposite knee by driving both towards the centre of the body.
Instruction.4: Spine might curve slightly but you should not shift your hips during the movement.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a good form.
Instruction.2: Send your hips back and start tilting the upper body.
Instruction.3: Maintain a straight back as you aim for your toes.
Instruction.4: Your range depends on your hamstring flexibility.

Instruction.1: Sit on a bench.
Instruction.2: Cross the ankle of one leg over the knee of the other.
Instruction.3: Press the knee of the crossed leg outwards.

Instruction.1: Sit on a bench.
Instruction.2: Cross the ankle of one leg over the knee of the other.
Instruction.3: Pull your knee toward  you and hold for a specified amount of time.

Instruction.1: Sit on a bench.
Instruction.2: Cross the ankle of one leg over the knee of the other.
Instruction.3: Push your knee away from you and lean forward for a specified amount of time.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back with bent knees and feet on the floor.
Instruction.2: Cross the ankle of your one leg over the knee of the other.
Instruction.3: Reach in between your legs, grabbing the thigh of the leg that is still on the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull that leg towards your chest.

WorkoutName: Glute Piriformis Mobilisation 1 Floor Seated Lacrosse Ball

Instruction.1: Sit on a massage ball distributing your weight between feet, palm and glute.
Instruction.2: Lean to the side and try to find a tight/painful spot while wiggling on the ball.
Instruction.3: Follow the pain as it shifts around your glute.

WorkoutName: Glute Stretch Knee Pull Dynamic Standing

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a good form.
Instruction.2: Alternate between pulling your knees towards you chest.
Instruction.3: Make sure you maintain an upright posture throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back.
Instruction.2: Bend one knee and pull it towards your chest.
Instruction.3: Maintain the stretch for a few seconds before swapping legs.

Instruction.1: Start on the 4 point position (on all fours).
Instruction.2: Straighten and raise one leg till it is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Make sure your spine remains in a neutral position.
Instruction.4: If you feel your lower back stiff or sore when performing this exercise, ask a trainer or therapist to guide you through.

Instruction.1: Start on the 4 point position (on all fours).
Instruction.2: Straighten and raise one leg till it is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Maintain the position but externally rotate the leg (knee aims out)
Instruction.4: If you feel your lower back stiff or sore when performing this exercise, ask a trainer or therapist to guide you through.

WorkoutName: Hip Extension External Rotation Pulses 4Pt Position

Instruction.1: Start on the 4 point position (on all fours).
Instruction.2: Straighten and raise one leg till it is parallel to the ground and externally rotate the leg (knee aims out).
Instruction.3: Perform small upward movements while maintaining the externally rotated position of the knee.
Instruction.4: Make sure your spine remains in a neutral position.

Instruction.1: Start on the 4 point position (on all fours).
Instruction.2: Straighten and raise one leg till it is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Make sure your spine remains in a neutral position.
Instruction.4: If you feel your lower back stiff or sore when performing this exercise, ask a trainer or therapist to guide you through.

WorkoutName: Prone Single Leg Hip Extension Hold

Instruction.1: Lie on your stomach.
Instruction.2: Secure your lower back by tilting your hips backwards.
Instruction.3: Raise one leg and hold the position for the specified duration.

Instruction.1: Attach a band to a fixed point. Wrap the loose end of the band around your ankle.
Instruction.2: Face the attachment point. Shift you weight onto one leg (use balancing aids if needed).
Instruction.3: Extend your working leg and maintain the position.

Instruction.1: From the standing position perform a walkout (use to palms to "walk" into the push up position).
Instruction.2: Bring your leg to the side and place the foot by your palm.
Instruction.3: Rotate towards the ceiling and then towards the ground, pressing the hips towards the ground.

Instruction.1: Attach a band to an anchor point and face away from the anchor point.
Instruction.2: Loop the other end of the band around your hips.
Instruction.3: While keeping your knees extended, shift your hips back, then forward against the band.

Instruction.1: From the standing position raise one knee till the thigh is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.2: Bring the knee to your side without rotating the hips.
Instruction.3: The knee drives the movement and the ankle lags slightly behind.

Instruction.1: Start from the standing position. Lower your body into a semi-squatted position.
Instruction.2: Push off the ground with two legs to perform the jump.
Instruction.3: Land on one leg, making sure to absorb the impact by bending the knee as much as needed.

WorkoutName: Jump Off Box Single Leg Landing

Instruction.1: Start from the standing position on a box. Lower your body into a semi-squatted position
Instruction.2: Push off the box with two legs to perform the jump.
Instruction.3: Land on one leg, on the ground, making sure to absorb the impact by bending the knee as much as needed.

Instruction.1: Start from the standing position. Lower your body into a semi-squatted position
Instruction.2: Push off the ground with two legs to perform the jump and land on the box. Jump off the box in the same manner
Instruction.3: Land on one leg, on the ground, making sure to absorb the impact by bending the knee as much as needed.
Instruction.4: Absorb the impact by bending the knees when landing. Try to maintain your balance

Instruction.1: Sit on your heels and reach out your arms on the floor while pressing the chest towards the ground.
Sit on your heels and reach out your arms on a box or foam roller while pressing the chest towards the ground.

WorkoutName: Side Step On And Off Box

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart. Your feet should be slightly pointed outward, and your shoulders should be down and relaxed.
Instruction.2: Place a step or box beside you, and step up onto it with one foot. Then bring the other foot to the box.

Instruction.1: From the standing position shift your weight onto the working leg and keep the other one suspended behind you
Instruction.2: Tilt at the hips and lean over as you are bending the loaded knee
Instruction.3: Bring your back knee close to the ground before standing back up.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a good form.
Instruction.2: Send your hips back and start tilting the upper body.
Instruction.3: Maintain a straight back as you aim for your toes.
Instruction.4: Lower the bar to the floor by bending your knees and keeping your back straight.

Instruction.1: Stand tall, hinge at hips, and reach hands to the floor.
Instruction.2: Walk hands forward into a plank position.
Instruction.3: Walk feet towards hands and repeat the motion.

Instruction.1: Lie down with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor.
Instruction.2: Push your hips up so that your butt is elevated and your back straight.
Instruction.3: Tense your glutes and raise your hips towards the ceiling.
Instruction.4: Once you are at the highest point you can manage, hold the position for a few seconds, and then slowly return to the starting position

Instruction.1: Tense your glutes and raise your hips towards the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Once you are at the highest point you can manage, hold the position for a few seconds, and then slowly return to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Push your hips up, so that your butt is elevated and your back straight.
Instruction.4: Lie down with one knee bent and and one with a slight bend.

WorkoutName: Bodyweight Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet on top of a sturdy box, bench or elevated surface.
Instruction.2: Drive through your heels to lift your hips off the floor, making sure to keep your feet and knees pointing forward.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet on top of a sturdy box, bench or elevated surface.
Instruction.2: Drive through your heels to lift your hips off the floor, making sure to keep your feet and knees pointing forward.

WorkoutName: Bodyweight Feet Elevated Single Leg Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet on top of a sturdy box, bench or elevated surface. Lift one leg off the box.
Instruction.2: Drive through your heel to lift your hips off the floor, making sure to keep your feet and knees pointing forward.

WorkoutName: Bodyweight Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet in a staggered position on the box.
Instruction.2: Drive through your heels to lift your hips off the floor, making sure to keep your feet and knees pointing forward.

Instruction.1: Take a slow, lateral step to the right.
Instruction.2: Extend the left knee, and drive your weight into your right side.
Instruction.3: Flex your knee and lower your body.
Instruction.4: Push back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Step forward with one leg.
Instruction.2: Lower your body until your rear knee nearly touches the ground.
Instruction.3: Ensure you remain upright, and your front knee stay above the front foot.
Instruction.4: Push off the floor with your front foot until you return to the starting position. Switch legs.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Start by doing a regular squat, then engage your core and jump up explosively.
Instruction.3: When you land, lower your body back into the squat position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet a little past shoulder width apart with a slight bend at your knee. Place your hands behind the back of your head.
Instruction.2: Keeping your back straight, rotate your hips to bring your shoulders down towards the floor. Stop when your chest is parallel with the floor.

Instruction.1: Grab a stick of some sort or hold onto something stable (rack, bench).
Instruction.2: Grab a box that is knee height or slightly lower.
Instruction.3: Hold the stick in your right arm and put your right leg on the box.
Instruction.4: Begin your squat by breaking at the knees. Get your knee close to the floor or all the way to the floor. Make sure to keep your chest tall.

Instruction.1: Step your left foot diagonally behind your right leg, crossing it behind your body. Bend your knees and lower your hips until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee is hovering just above the ground.
Instruction.2: Push through your right foot to straighten your legs and return to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat the movement with your other leg.

Instruction.1: Step forward with one leg and lower your body until your front thigh is parallel to the floor and your back knee almost touches the ground. Keep your chest up and your front foot flat on the floor.
Instruction.2: Push through your front foot to straighten your legs and return to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat the movement with your other leg.

Instruction.1: Place your heels on a plate or very low step.
Instruction.2: Keep your chest tall and initiate the squat by pushing your hips back and breaking at the knees.
Instruction.3: You should notice yourself able to squat lower than normal.

Instruction.1: Engage your core by drawing your belly button towards your spine. This will help to stabilize your body.
Instruction.2: Take a large step to the side with your right foot, planting it firmly on the ground.
Instruction.3: As you step, bend your right knee and lower your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. Your left leg should remain straight.
Instruction.4: Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat on the opposite side by stepping out with your left foot.

Instruction.1: Take a split stance. Make sure to keep your chest tall.
Instruction.2: Bring your rear knee to the floor or close to it.
Instruction.3: Drive through your front heel and your rear foot back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start standing with your feet hip-width apart. Lower your body into a squat position, placing your hands on the ground in front of you.
Instruction.2: Quickly jump your feet back into a plank position, keeping your body in a straight line from your head to your toes.
Instruction.3: Perform a push-up, keeping your core tight and your elbows close to your body.
Instruction.4: Jump your feet back towards your hands, and then jump up into the air, reaching your arms overhead.
Instruction.5: Land softly and immediately lower your body back into the squat position to repeat the movement.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box.
Instruction.2: *Start with a low box if this is your first time*
Instruction.3: Sink into a quarter of half squat and then pop your hips forward.
Instruction.4: Try to land in the middle of the box as softly as possible to minimise impact on your joints.

Instruction.1: Stand on top of a box. Step off of the box and land on the floor.
Instruction.2: Land as softly as possible. Squat as you land to minimise impact on your joints.
Instruction.3: Go straight into another hop after you've landed. This will help you learn to absorb impact.

Instruction.1: Setup two boxes. One to jump on and one to sit.
Instruction.2: Go from a seated position and pop your hips forward forcefully.
Instruction.3: Jump and land on the box softly.

Instruction.1: Get down on all fours and position your hands under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Instruction.2: Kick back with one leg and squeeze your glutes.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position by bending your knee and lowering your leg.
Instruction.4: Switch Legs. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Place the barbell on your back
Instruction.2: Step your foot back and around while simultaneously bringing the weight down.
Instruction.3: Return to start and repeat on other leg.

Instruction.1: Start in a standing position.
Instruction.2: Lunge forward, switch legs mid-air.
Instruction.3: Land and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet together.
Instruction.2: Step back with right foot.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position, then lunge with left foot.

WorkoutName: Bodyweight Figure Four Heels Elevated Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Start by lying on a bench with your foot resting on top of a box,  and cross one leg over the other.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the box.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Put your shoulder blades on a bench. Both feet on a low box or a plate.
Instruction.2: Start with your hips up.
Instruction.3: Drop your hips and then push your hips up toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Abduct at the hips and raise your leg out to the side.
Instruction.2: Return to the starting position and stop just short of your foot touching back to the ground (to keep tension on the muscle).

Instruction.1: Start with a shoulder width stance.
Instruction.2: Jump laterally and fall into a squat. Tap the ground.
Instruction.3: Jump the opposite direction

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width.
Instruction.2: Step forward with your right foot and bend both knees to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Step back with the same leg until the back knee taps the floor.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell in goblet position.
Instruction.2: Squat down to parallel depth and then halfway back up.
Instruction.3: Stay in this short range of motion for the duration of the set.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width.
Instruction.2: Step forward with your right foot and bend both knees to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Step back with the same leg until the back knee taps the floor.

WorkoutName: Bodyweight Single Leg Heels Elevated Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Start by lying on a bench with your foot on a plate or low box.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and hold a pole overhead, using an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Begin the squat by bending at the hips and knees, keeping your core tight and the dumbbells balanced overhead.
Instruction.3: Lower your body as far as you can while keeping the dumbbells overhead, then push back up to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, making sure to keep your back straight, chest lifted, and the dumbbells stable overhead throughout the entire movement.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Start by doing a regular squat, then engage your core and jump up explosively.
Instruction.3: Narrow your stance while in the air, and land softly. Go directly into another rep.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Start by doing a regular squat, tap the floor, then engage your core and jump up explosively.
Instruction.3: Bring your feet mostly together, tap your toes back to the floor, then bring your feet back their original width.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent and raise one leg.
Instruction.2: Without changing the bend in your knee, bend at your hips, and lower your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Tense your glutes and then bring yourself back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your back to a bench (or raised surface) and place one of your feet on the bench.
Instruction.2: Squat down until your front leg is about parallel to the floor.
Instruction.3: Go back to the starting position. After completing the desired amount of reps, switch legs and repeat.

Instruction.1: Lie down with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor.
Instruction.2: Push your hips up so that your butt is elevated and your back straight.
Instruction.3: Tense your glutes and raise your hips towards the ceiling.
Instruction.4: Once you are at the highest point you can manage, hold the position for a few seconds, and raise one leg off the ground.
Instruction.5: Lower slowly to the start position.

WorkoutName: Glute Bridge Isometric Hold Single Alternate

Instruction.1: Lie on your back. Bend your knees so your feet are flat on the floor with heels under knees
Instruction.2: Push through your heels into the ground, lifting your hips up to the point where there is a straight line from your chest to your knees. Squeeze your bum at the top of the movement
Instruction.3: Maintain the top position and extend one leg at the time.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back with knees slightly bent and heels dug in.
Instruction.2: Perform a posterior pelvic tilt (flatten your lower back on the ground).
Instruction.3: Press the heels into the ground to raise your hips off it.
Instruction.4: Hold the position for the specified duration.

WorkoutName: Hamstring Bridge With Elevated Legs Box Bilateral

Instruction.1: Lie on your back. Place your heels on a box or bench, having a 90° angle at hips and knees.
Instruction.2: Perform a posterior pelvic tilt (flatten your lower back against the ground).
Instruction.3: Push through your heels into the box, lifting your hips up to the point where there is a straight line from your chest to your knees.

WorkoutName: Hamstring Bridge With Elevated Legs Box Unilateral

Instruction.1: Lie on your back. Place one heel on a box or bench, having a 90° angle at hip and knee.
Instruction.2: Perform a posterior pelvic tilt (flatten your lower back against the ground).
Instruction.3: Push through your heel into the box, lifting your hips up to the point where there is a straight line from your chest to your knees.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, one foot slightly behind.
Instruction.2: Lower into a squat, keeping weight on front heel.
Instruction.3: Return to standing, engaging glutes and core.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: flex your knees and hips and sit back into the squat while lowering your body
Instruction.3: Continue down to full depth
Instruction.4: Return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Sit with one leg in front of you flat on the ground.
Instruction.2: While the other leg is to your side, also flat on the ground with your foot pointed backwards.
Instruction.3: Hold this position for the prescribed amount of time then change sides.

Instruction.1: Stand on one leg, extend the other forward for balance.
Instruction.2: Lower into a squat, keeping your chest up and core tight.
Instruction.3: Press through your heel to stand back up, repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start.

Instruction.1: Place your foot on a plate or a low box.
Instruction.2: Put all of your weight on your front foot and lean forward.
Instruction.3: Lower until your calves touch your hamstrings and then extend back up.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, keeping bar stable throughout.

Instruction.1: Lie face-down on a stability ball, hips centered, feet anchored, hands behind your head.
Instruction.2: Engage your core, lift your upper body until aligned with legs, keeping your neck neutral.
Instruction.3: Lower your torso slowly back to the starting position, maintaining control and steady breathing.

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet resting on top of a ball.
Instruction.2: Push through your heels and raise your hips towards the ceiling, keeping your feet flat on the bar.
Instruction.3: Engage your glutes at the top of the movement, pause briefly and then lower your hips back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Sit on the floor, place upper back on a stability ball, feet flat, knees bent.
Instruction.2: Drive hips upward by squeezing glutes, forming a straight line from shoulders to knees.
Instruction.3: Lower hips slowly without touching the floor, maintaining core engagement, then repeat.

Instruction.1: Lie face down on a stability ball, hands on the floor, legs extended straight.
Instruction.2: Engage glutes and lower back, raising legs until aligned with your torso.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower legs back down without touching the ground, maintaining core engagement. Repeat.

WorkoutName: Stability Ball Single Leg Hip Thrust

Instruction.1: Lie on the ball, one foot on the ground.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg off the ground and engage your glutes to raise your hips up towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Stability Ball Straight Leg Glute Bridge

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, heels on a stability ball, legs straight, arms by your sides.
Instruction.2: Press through your heels, lift hips, engage glutes and core, forming a straight line.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower hips, maintaining control, then repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, placing a stability ball between your lower back and wall.
Instruction.2: Slowly squat down by bending knees to 90 degrees, keeping back straight and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Press through heels, straighten legs, and return to standing while maintaining balance and control.

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Laying on the floor with your knees bent and feet firmly on the floor, rest the kettlebell on your pelvis.
Instruction.2: Pushing through the legs and keeping the core muscles engaged, raise your pelvis off the floor until your stomach, pelvis and thighs make a straight line.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower to the ground to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Laying on the floor with one knee bent with the foot firmly on the floor and one leg extended, rest the kettlebell on your pelvis.
Instruction.2: Pushing through the bent leg and keeping the core muscles engaged, raise your pelvis and the extended leg off the floor until your stomach, pelvis and thighs make a straight line.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower to the ground to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Sitting on the floor with your knees bent and feet planted firmly on the floor, lean your back against the bench.
Instruction.2: Resting the kettlebell on your pelvis, raise your pelvis until your stomach, pelvis and thighs are in line.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower until you are in the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Sitting on the floor with one knee bent with the foot firmly on the floor and one leg extended, lean your back against the bench.
Instruction.2: Resting the kettlebell on your pelvis, raise your pelvis until your stomach, pelvis and thighs are in line.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower until you are in the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, swing kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.3: Swing kettlebell up, switch hands at the top, and repeat in a fluid motion.

Instruction.1: Start with kettlebells between legs.
Instruction.2: Swing kettlebells up to shoulder.
Instruction.3: Press kettlebells overhead.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend at hips and knees to lift kettlebells.
Instruction.3: Stand tall, then lower.

Instruction.1: Begin with a two kettlebells between your legs, hinge at hips, then swing it upwards explosively.
Instruction.2: As they rise, lock out arm overhead, wrist straight.
Instruction.3: Control the descent, then repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebells outside legs
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, swing kettlebells forward, then back.
Instruction.3: Thrust hips to swing kettlebells upward, keeping arms straight.

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebell at your side.
Instruction.2: Step forward, lunge, and return.
Instruction.3: Repeat with opposite leg.

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebells in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step back and lunge diagonally.

Instruction.1: Start with kettlebells in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step forward into lunge.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebell in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step sideways into a lunge position.
Instruction.3: Return to start position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Start with kettlebell in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step back into lunge.
Instruction.3: Return to start position.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Front Rack Single Arm Lateral Lunge

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebells close to chest.
Instruction.2: Squat down, keeping chest up.
Instruction.3: Stand up, extending hips fully.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, grip kettlebell, and swing it overhead.
Instruction.3: Extend hips and knees, lock out arms at the top.

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebells in front of you.
Instruction.2: Step sideways, lunge down and let the kettlebells land between your legs.
Instruction.3: Push off, return to start. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebells at your side.
Instruction.2: Step backward, lower body.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding kettlebells in front.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, keeping back straight, and lower kettlebells towards ground.
Instruction.3: Return to start position, squeezing glutes at the top.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Clean And Press

Instruction.1: Begin with the kettlebell between your legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at your hips, and lift to shoulder, then press overhead.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Forward Lunge
Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Reverse Lunge

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell between legs, grip with one hand, hinge at hips.
Instruction.2: Swing kettlebell forcefully forward, using hip thrust, arm straight.
Instruction.3: Swing kettlebell back between legs, repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Begin with feet hip-width apart, one foot forward, kettlebell between feet.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, grip kettlebell, and stand tall.
Instruction.3: Lower kettlebell with control, then repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet wide apart, toes pointing slightly outward, and kettlebell on the floor between your feet.
Instruction.2: Bend at hips and knees, keeping back straight, and grip the kettlebell handle.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell by extending hips and knees, stand up straight, and return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start with a kettlebell between your legs, hinge at hips, swing it upward.
Instruction.2: Lift kettlebell to chest level, elbows high, engaging shoulders.
Instruction.3: Lower kettlebell back down, maintaining control. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold kettlebells at your shoulders.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a kettlebell at one shoulder.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Step Up Balance

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a kettlebell in one hand
Instruction.2: Place your right foot on the box and push through the heel to lift your body up and onto the box, keeping your left foot off the ground.
Instruction.3: Step back down with your right foot, lowering your left foot to the ground.

Instruction.1: Standing up straight, using a bench as a step, raise one foot onto the bench and hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the straight leg.
Instruction.2: Stand and bring both feet onto the bench. Slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell between your legs, with your knees slightly bent.
Instruction.2: Keeping your back straight, swing the kettlebell upwards until the kettlebell is level with your chest and carefully lower.
Instruction.3: Repeat

Instruction.1: Stand straight with your feet slightly apart and hold a kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Bring the same leg as the arm holding the kettlebell in front of you, squat down until your thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Hold the weight tucked into your upper chest area, keeping your elbows in. Your feet should be slightly wider than your shoulders.
Instruction.2: Sink down into the squat, keeping your elbows inside the track of your knees.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels while keeping your chest up and return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees and keep your back straight.
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your chest.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips keeping your back and knees straight and the kettlebell close to your chest.
Instruction.3: Return to standing position and thrust your pelvis forward.

Instruction.1: Stand straight with your feet shoulder width apart. Keep your back straight and hold the kettlebell in front of your pelvis.
Instruction.2: Take a large step to one side, holding the kettlebell low and lunge into the bent leg.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position and repeat

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, lifting one foot off the floor behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the lifted leg.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you extend your lifted leg behind you, keeping your back straight - holding out your arm to the side for balance.
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand straight with your feet slightly apart and hold a kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Bring the same leg as the arm holding the kettlebell behind you, squat down until your back knee touches the ground, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Hold the weight tucked into your upper chest area, keeping your elbows in. Your feet should be slightly wider than your shoulders and the heels slightly raised on a surface.
Instruction.2: Sink down into the squat, keeping your elbows inside the track of your knees.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels while keeping your chest up and return to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Standing up straight, using a bench as a step, raise one foot onto the bench and hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the straight leg.
Instruction.2: Stand and bring both feet onto the bench. Slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a kettlebell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the kettlebell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the kettlebell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the kettlebell on the opposite side of your body.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, one foot slightly behind. Hold kettlebell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Lower into a squat, keeping weight on front heel.
Instruction.3: Return to standing, engaging glutes and core.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a box or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart with a kettlebell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Lower your body into a squat position, sitting back onto the box and pausing for a moment before standing back up.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels to return to the standing position.

Instruction.1: Hold a kettlebell at your chest, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step one leg diagonally back into a lunge.
Instruction.3: Alternate legs, keeping your chest up and core engaged.

Instruction.1: Stand tall, holding kettlebells by your sides, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step forward with one leg, lowering until both knees form 90° angles.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start, and switch legs.

Instruction.1: Hold one kettlebell with one or both hands, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step out to one side, bending the knee.
Instruction.3: Push off, return to center, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Hold two kettlebells by your side.
Instruction.2: Take a big step backwards with your left leg, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground and your right knee is bent at a 90-degree angle.
Instruction.3: Push back up and switch legs, alternating each rep.

Instruction.1: Grab a stick of some sort or hold onto something stable (rack, bench).
Instruction.2: Grab a box that is knee height or slightly lower.
Instruction.3: Hold the stick in your right arm, kettlebell in the other and put your right leg on the box.
Instruction.4: Begin your squat by breaking at the knees. Get your knee close to the floor or all the way to the floor. Make sure to keep your chest tall.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width. Kettlebell at your side.
Instruction.2: Step forward with your right foot and bend both knees to lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Step back with the same leg until the back knee taps the floor.

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, kettlebells in each hand, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Front Rack Deficit Reverse Lunge

Instruction.1: Stand on a platform, kettlebells in front rack position, feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Step back, lowering knee toward floor, keeping chest upright and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Push through front foot, return to start.

Instruction.1: Place your foot on a plate or a low box. Hold two kettlebells in each hand.
Instruction.2: Put all of your weight on your front foot and lean forward.
Instruction.3: Lower until your calves touch your hamstrings and then extend back up.

Instruction.1: Set up a bar at mid way up your quad. Place the working leg against the bar.
Instruction.2: Place one foot behind. You should only be on your toes on that back foot. Your front foot should be planted flat the entire time.
Instruction.3: Bend your back knee and push your hips back. Look for a stretch in your front hamstring.
Instruction.4: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward again until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place a barbell at about midway up your thigh. Press your quads into the barbell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knees mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Half Kneeling Goblet Romanian Deadlift

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a kettlebell in a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Place one knee on a bench and hold a kettlebell.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while leaving your knee mostly extended. Look for a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.3: When you feel the stretch, push your hips forward until you're back in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Get into a quadruped position. Loop the band around both of your wrists and one of your feet.
Instruction.2: Extend your knee and hip straight back until you feel like contraction in the glutes.
Instruction.3: Flex at the knee until back in the starting position.

Instruction.1: Attach the band around your ankle. Stand with feet hip-width apart, feet facing forward, and hands on hips.
Instruction.2: Lift your right leg away from your body to the side, keeping your knee straight. This is your starting position.
Instruction.3: Maintaining proper form, move your right leg as far to the side as you can, keeping your left leg planted firmly on the ground. Hold for a second and then return your right leg to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Attach a band to a stable anchor point, such as a door handle or post.
Instruction.2: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your ankles.
Instruction.3: Keeping your feet together, move your legs out to the sides and then back to the midline of your body. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

Instruction.1: Anchor a band to a stable point.
Instruction.2: Place the loops of the band behind your knees.
Instruction.3: Perform a normal squat and extend your knees against the band at the top.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band at hip level. Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back while keeping your back flat until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with your head by the anchor point of the band, which should be 6 to 12 inches above your head
Instruction.2: Place the band around your midfoot and extend at the knees and hip.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to the lowest point possible. Straddle the band and then grab with both hands.
Instruction.2: Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Instruction.3: Push your butt back until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. Then extend the hips back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand on your band with both feet.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips while keeping a flat back.
Instruction.3: Hinge until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Instruction.4: Push your hips back forward until you are in a standing position.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width grip. Both feet should be on the band with the band loops in each of your hand.
Instruction.2: Push your butt back and also break at the knees.
Instruction.3: Try to hit parallel depth (bottom of your leg should be parallel with the ground). If you can't tell your squat depth, then try squatting in front of a mirror and watch your form.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a stable point.
Instruction.2: Take a half squat position and hold there.
Instruction.3: Perform a row while holding the squat position.

WorkoutName: Band Squat Hold Single Arm Row

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a stable point and take a half squat position.
Instruction.2: Hold the band loop in one hand and pull your elbow straight back.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width grip. Both feet should be on the band with the band looped over both hands.
Instruction.2: Push your butt back and also break at the knees.
Instruction.3: Try to hit parallel depth (bottom of your leg should be parallel with the ground). If you can't tell your squat depth, then try squatting in front of a mirror and watch your form.

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you.
Instruction.2: Place a block under your left knee, then bend your right knee and stack it on top of your left ankle.
Instruction.3: Flex both feet and gently press your knees towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your hips.
Instruction.4: Hold the pose for a few breaths, then switch sides and repeat.

Instruction.1: Extend your right leg behind you and place your right ankle on top of your left thigh, with your right knee pointing out to the side.
Instruction.2: Sitting up straight, use your hands to gently press down on your right knee while at the same time pulling your left buttock back.
Instruction.3: Hold for 5-10 deep breaths, then release and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Start in a seated position with your legs extended in front of you.
Instruction.2: Cross your right leg over your left leg, placing your right foot on the floor beside your left hip.
Instruction.3: Cross your left leg over your right leg, placing your left foot on the floor beside your right hip.
Instruction.4: Relax your arms by your sides or place them on your abdomen and take deep breaths.

Instruction.1: Sit on a yoga mat with legs straight in front of you.
Instruction.2: Bend the right knee and place the right foot on top of the left thigh. Allow the right knee to fall towards the floor.
Instruction.3: Bring the left foot onto the right thigh. Keep the spine straight and rest hands on the knees.
Instruction.4: Hold for several breaths and then release.

Instruction.1: Adjust seat and handlebar height for comfort and proper posture on the assault bike.
Instruction.2: Start pedaling with even, controlled motion, maintaining your desired resistance level.
Instruction.3: Monitor heart rate and intensity; increase or decrease resistance for an effective cardio workout.

Instruction.1: Get the treadmill up to a comfortable speed where you are doing a light jog.
Get the treadmill up to a speed where you are doing a sprint.
Get the treadmill up to a comfortable speed where you are doing a walk.
Perform a jumping jack while crossing the feet.
Perform s sprint in a figure eight pattern.
Instruction.2: Make sure to stay low.

Instruction.1: Do a light hop and split your stance.
Instruction.2: Land lightly on your toes, and then bring the opposing leg forward.

Instruction.1: Bring one leg forward and then the other.
Instruction.2: Bring the original leg backwards and then the other.

WorkoutName: Cardio In In Out Out Shuffle

Instruction.1: Start with your feet side by side.
Instruction.2: Bring one foot laterally, then the other.
Instruction.3: Return the first foot to its starting position, then the other.

Instruction.1: Face sideways on the treadmill.
Instruction.2: Take a quarter squat position with a wide stance.
Instruction.3: Shuffle sideways for a specified amount of time, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Start with a shoulder width stance.
Instruction.2: Stay on your toes, step right, tap your left toe to the ground, plant your right foot and raise your left leg.
Instruction.3: Then repeat in the opposite direction.

Instruction.1: Stand upright, feet together, facing forward, ready to move laterally.
Instruction.2: Move right foot behind left, then step left foot to the side.
Instruction.3: Alternate crossing and stepping, increase speed, maintain rhythm and balance.

Instruction.1: Start with a shoulder width stance.
Instruction.2: Quickly tap your feet while moving laterally.

Instruction.1: Start with a wide stance.
Instruction.2: Shuffle sideways for a specified distance while maintaining a quarter squat position.

Instruction.1: Stand feet shoulder-width, knees slightly bent, arms behind you, eyes forward.
Instruction.2: Swing arms backward, squat deeply, loading legs for explosive power.
Instruction.3: Swing arms, explode forward, extend legs mid-air, land softly on both feet.

Instruction.1: Stand feet shoulder-width, knees slightly bent, arms behind you, eyes forward.
Instruction.2: Swing arms backward, squat deeply, loading legs for explosive power.
Instruction.3: Swing arms, explode forward, extend legs mid-air, land softly on both feet.
Instruction.4: Shuffle back to the starting position.

WorkoutName: Cardio Row Erg Rower Four Stroke Sprint Start

Instruction.1: Sit on seat, feet strapped in, grip handle with arms extended.
Instruction.2: Push with legs, lean back slightly. Do four small pulls with increasing distance on each rep.
Instruction.3: Extend arms, lean forward from hips, bend knees to return to start.

WorkoutName: Cardio Row Erg Rower Legs Only

Instruction.1: Strap your feet in tightly.
Instruction.2: Keep your arms extended while flexing and extending at the hips and knees.

Instruction.1: Set up two cones at a specified distance.
Instruction.2: Stay low and sprint quickly to the second cone.
Instruction.3: Hinge forward and tap the cone, then turn and sprint to the original cone.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired time or reps.

Instruction.1: Stand, balance on right foot, left foot behind, slightly bent knees.
Instruction.2: Jump to left, landing on left foot, right foot behind, swinging arms.
Instruction.3: Continue leaping side-to-side, maintaining balance and speed, like a speed skater.

WorkoutName: Cardio Skater To Single Leg Burpee

Instruction.1: Leap sideways, land on right foot, left leg behind to the side.
Instruction.2: Drop into a single-leg burpee, right leg only, hands to ground.
Instruction.3: Return to standing on right, leap sideways to left, repeat with left leg.

Instruction.1: Stand tall, feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent, ready to move.
Instruction.2: Quickly drive knees up towards chest, alternating legs, pumping arms in rhythm.
Instruction.3: Gradually speed up, maintaining high knees and arm movement, breathe steadily.

Instruction.1: Stand tall, feet together, arms by sides, ready to move.
Instruction.2: Step right foot out, simultaneously raise arms above head.
Instruction.3: Step right foot in, lower arms, repeat left, maintain rhythm.

Instruction.1: Hold the handles and maintain a neutral spine.
Instruction.2: Pedal at a moderate pace and try to minimise rocking back and forth.

Instruction.1: Step onto the pedals, grip the handles, and start moving your feet in a natural stride.
Instruction.2: Adjust resistance and incline for desired intensity while maintaining a steady, controlled motion.
Instruction.3: Keep your posture upright, engage your core, and maintain a consistent pace for an effective workout.

Instruction.1: Stand with the band looped under both feet and the other end of the band in both hands in an overhead press position.
Instruction.2: Do a light hop and bring both feet outward while pressing the band overhead.

Instruction.1: Grab the band with a double overhand grip. Bring both feet outward while performing a little hop.
Instruction.2: As you hop, pull the band apart.

Instruction.1: Loop a band around your back. Start with both arms extended at your side.
Instruction.2: As you perform the jack. Bring both arms together and make a little clap.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet together, arms in front at chest level, palms touching.
Instruction.2: Spread legs wide, simultaneously swing arms out to sides, palms facing forward.
Instruction.3: Jump back to starting position, bringing arms together again quickly. Repeat rhythmically.
